txt.en: 'The Uruk-hai must have some information we can use.'
Tham Celechir can be found north-east of Idhobel.\n\nHaerlendir has asked you to defeat Uruk-hai at Tham Celechir.
The Uruk dropped a strange parchment. The markings are unfamiliar to you.\n\nShow the parchment to Haerlendir on the road south of Tham Celechir.
This parchment must have more information.
Deliver the parchment to Rhovandis at Idhobel
'What news do you bring from Tham Celechir?'
Haerlendir asked you to show the strange parchment to Rhovandis in Idhobel.\n\nReturn to Rhovandis.
Talk to Haerlendir

'This parchment resembles that of many carried by the Uruk-hai. It likely contains valuable information, but the scribblings are indecipherable to me.\n\n'This may be what we've been looking for. I'm sure if you let Rhovandis have a look, she may be able to glean some information from it.'
Deliver the parchment to Rhovandis at Idhobel

'Thank you for your help [placeholder]. The markings on this parchment are familiar to me. It contains information regarding the movement of the wargs into Western Eregion. A master of beasts musters north-east of Tham Celechir tasked with bringing more wargs into these lands.\n\n'If we can defeat this master, we can slow the White Handâ€™s approach on Caras Gelebren, and slow the unfurling shadow.'
Deliver the parchment to Rhovandis
You gave the parchment to Rhovandis
Defeat the Uruk-hai captain
Defeated Uruks ([placeholder]/[placeholder])
Find the source of the Warg threat.
Obtain information by defeating Uruks ([placeholder]/[placeholder])
The Uruk dropped a strange parchment

'The White Hand grows bold. We must be wary. The presence of wargs within Uruk-hai camps is troubling. We will have to see if there is more we can gather from the Uruk-hai to understand their true purpose.\n\n'Return to Tham Celechir and see if you can find any information from the Uruk-hai that will lead us to the source of this warg threat.'
Reveal the Unfettered
Obtain information from Uruk-hai
Look for an Uruk-hai captain within Tham Celechir.
